Class RouteData

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<TimeObject>

    public class RouteData
extends TimeObject
    Represents a route of a Race

    The static method subscribe(com.tractrac.clientmodule.Race, com.tractrac.clientmodule.data.ICallbackData<com.tractrac.clientmodule.Route, com.tractrac.clientmodule.data.RouteData>) can be used to receive positions.

    Custom data may be attached to each class instance.

      • subscribe

        public static com.maptrack.client.io.TypeController subscribe(Race race,
                                              ICallbackData<Route,RouteData> callback)
        Sets up a subscription for the route of a given Race.

        The method returns immediately and the data are subsequently sent to a given callback, as they are received.

        The returned type controller should be added to a DataController.

        Parameters:
        race - the race from which to request the data
        callback - the callback to receive the data
        Returns:
        the type controller
